719294f-a.title: Manhattan: Delancey Street - Columbia Street
719294f-a.text:
DDDalancey Street, north side, east from but not including Columbia,
to, and including Cannon Streets. No. 280 Delancey Street, adjoining
the N.W. corner of Cannon Street, is a 3-story frame house.
1932.
J. Clarence Davies Collection, Museum of the City of Hew York.
Negative No. 396.
The corner structure adjacent to the frame building is to be
demolished by the New York City Housing Authority, according to the
New York Sun of September 12, 1938. This building bears No's. 282
Delancey Street and 47 Cannon Street.
